Machine chamfered loading port opening

Standard features include Uni-Line™stock and receiver design for instinctive eye/rib alignment; stock drop spacer system for customizing fit;  drilled and tapped receiver; interchangeable ACCU-CHOKE™system; durable black synthetic stock and forend; and matte blue metal finishes.

Performance-enhancing features on the JM Pro Series include Mossberg’s extended tactical bolt handle; forend cut to facilitate faster reloads; oversized safety button; orange magazine follower; and protective barrel clamp for the extended mag tube. title: For Sale/Trade:  A Challenge To AR and AK Sellers At SHTF Prices.
location: ALL, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
Earlier this month I sold my AR15 for $1600 which I felt was probably $400 higher then
it would have sold for 90 days earlier.  I decided to keep $1200 and sent a check in the amount of a $400 donation to the NRA.  I have been investing in guns for 40 years with the main intent of resale at a later time.  So I understand and have practiced the rule of buy low, sell high.  But this shouldn't be about putting extra greenbacks in your wallet. It's a time to reinvest your profits to fight for OUR 2nd amendment.  I have to say, it was more gratifying to write that check then it was seeing the profit in my bank account.

With that all said, I challenge all sellers to invest some small portion of their gain in a donation to the NRA as they are OUR only voice in Washington. 

If this idea caught on across the Armslist community, coast to coast,  I rest assure we would strengthen the NRA to extinguish this nonsense.
